<strong>1. Computer Store</strong>

Write a program that prints you a receipt for a new computer. 
You will recieve the parts' prices (without tax) until you recieve what type of client it is regular or special
tax 20% for each item you recieve
if special - 10% discount from total price with taxes


<strong>2. The Lift</strong>

Write a program that finds a place for tourist on a lift.
Every wagon should have a maximum of 4 people on it. If a wagon is full, you should direct the people to the next one with space available


<strong>3. Memory Game</strong>

Write a program that recreates the Memory game.
You will recieve a sequence of elements. Each element in the sequence will have a twin
Until command "End" we will recieve string with two integers separated by space, representing the indexes of elements in the sequence
If two equal indexes are entered or indexes which are out of bounds of the sequence, you should add two matching elements at the middle of the sequence.
